                    <h2>Changes</h2>
                    <div class="revisionsKey">
                      Key:&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="diffAdd">Additions</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="diffRemove">Deletions</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div id="versionCompareContent" class="WPC-editableContent">
                    <font size="2"><b><font size="3">There are some things that just can&#39;t be avoided...<br>
                    <br></font></b> Some of the Pioneers noticed that there were some forces that they couldn&#39;t control in the new world, they called those &quot;Laws&quot; and were writen by Murphylus Hazzard. This is the most up to date list; if you come up with a law that you know must be writen here, post it in a thread and we&#39;ll add it.<br>
                    <br></font> <font face="Courier" size="2"><b>Murphy&#39;s Laws of the New World</b></font>
                    <ul>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Your resser will be amongst the first to die.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">No matter what, you can&#39;t win against lag.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The chance of an enchanting rolling blank or useless is directly proportional to the cost of the chip or the desire of patron.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Even on the carebear servers deceit, under handiness, bloodlust, and power mongering still reign.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Bots on the same router flock together.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Just because you reported a bot ages ago, doesn&#39;t mean they won&#39;t be expert before you.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The difficulty of leveling a stance is directly proportional to the level of the stance and the character.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The really valuable items don&#39;t have a sound effect when they drop.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Your last enchant chip will always disappoint you.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Shoes tend to enchant with Evasion.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">30% of all of the weapon drops are bracelets.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">40% of all of the armor drops are robes.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">During a lobby the highly desired drop(s) usually go to the person that requires it the least, and is the least likely to offer it to those who do.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">In Colony War permanent alliances, aren&#39;t.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">There&#39;s never enough room in your Quarters.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">There&#39;s never enough slots in your Saved Warp List.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">There&#39;s never enough space in your Storage with Leo.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">You never have enough vis.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">If you don&#39;t pick it up, a bot surely will.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">If a box spawns near you, there&#39;s always someone there to shot it.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">You tend die on the hardest part of the quest because of the lag monster.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">You always get something you think as worthless when your low level, but don&#39;t get it when your high level.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Selling Cash Shop items for vis is always better then giving your credit card to bots.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Your characters will sometimes die when you look away for 30 seconds.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">You&#39;ll be able to semi AFK fine all day while at your computer, but die as soon as you go use the bathroom. [Read the following laws as to why / how!]<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Mobs that can&#39;t KO (knockout) your toons when you are active, will gain super powers as soon as you go AFK.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The box appears more frequently after you AFK.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The boss spawns just after you AFK.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The PK approaches soon after you AFK.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">You&#39;ll run out of ammo 3 hours after you AFK.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The value loot drops while you are AFK.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The value loot vanishes the moment you resume from AFK.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Catherine&#39;s hip always drops from the first Lloyd after you AFK.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Your AFK spot will likely be taken when you leave to resupply, revive, or do a trade. Or even while your still there!<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">While AFK in Rion, the purple cockatrice will <b><u><i>always</i></u></b> find you!<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The purple cockatrice of Rion will follow you all around the map without fail, you can run but you just can&#39;t hide!<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Maintenance happens 30 minutes after your ready for a long gaming session.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">No matter how high you level, there&#39;s always another character that needs another.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">You can spend 20 hours looking for a hip, all you can get is a hand.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">There are no elites for summoners.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">No pics, then it didn&#39;t happen.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The item(s) that you want to buy the most are rarely available for sale at a reasonable price.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">NPCs, uncontrolled characters, and camera angles rarely cooperates when taking a screen shot or making a video.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The vowel O does not exist in the New World, where as G&#39;s and E&#39;s can be found in the hundreds. How they spell in the New W0rld is a mystery.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">When asking directions, over here is not over there.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Even with 20 Upgrade Accelerators there is no such thing as a 100% chance of success when strengthening an item to +5.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">You always remember to restock AFTER you enter the 500K section of Fire Isle Zone... This also applies to after you enter the Relics Underground / Sacred Dungeon.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The most wanted mods go on random weapons you pick up.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">If you have kids, they will always crave attention at the moment a Boss spawns or you get mobbed and need to spawn skills.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">If you have cats, they will always crave attention at the moment a Boss spawns or you get mobbed and need to spawn skills.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The recipes/Elites you do find will 50% of the time be the ones you: A ) Already have or don&#39;t need. Or B ) Be Cannons/Shotguns.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Just because the area says 84+ doesn&#39;t mean you will actually FIND any level 84+ loot.</font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times"><span class="diffAdd">Unarmed Scouts when put on Defend Mode, heals you when you don&#39;t need it, and doesn&#39;t when you&#39;re dying.</span></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times"><span class="diffAdd">When in tournaments, your scout will never heal itself when it needs to, and will heal itself when it has max HP...</span></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Scouts will serve no purpose at higher levels. [Mostly because the ones are present in the higher level, usually end up dead anyways.]<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">When in an area with flying mobs, don&#39;t use skills, or else the flying mobs will attack!<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">No matter how much tax money a clan has received, the members will always be so poor that they have to farm weak Bosses for stuff to sell.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">While you are trying to aggro a raid boss, some n00b will never understand &quot;don&#39;t attack until the tank says go.&quot;<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The monster you are looking for will not show up until you don&#39;t need to exterminate them anymore.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">The Drama Llama has many tenders.<br></font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">Exceptions to the Laws are no longer applicable after you begin to rely on those exceptions.</font></li>
                      <li><font face="Times" size="3">When in tournaments, your scout will never heal itself when it needs to, and will heal itself when it has max HP...</font></li>
                    </ul><font color="#FF0000" size="1"><br>
                    Note: <span class="diffRemove">El_Hazzard</span><span class="diffAdd">El_Hazard</span> made this list on the official forum, you can <span class="diffAdd"></span></font><font size="1">see it here.</font><br>
                    <font size="2"><br></font>
